description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking for your next leadership role?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Does the prospect of exploring, leading and delivering integrated care for patients excite you?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If the answer to these questions is yes, we are eager to hear from you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are recruiting an ambitious Primary Care Network Lead to lead our established specialist services in Rushcliffe. Applicants will need to demonstrate passion, creativity and deliver a team vision which supports both high quality proactive and responsive care for the people of Rushcliffe. Applicants will also demonstrate the ability to embrace the needs of an innovative and fast changing local health economy and provide leadership and day to day support to community multidisciplinary teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return, we will provide you with an individually tailored induction programme with ongoing and additional local and organisational development and supervision to build up your portfolio of leadership skills and knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be a registered professional, with recent community clinical practice and experience of working in a multi professional team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A full UK driving licence and vehicle for business use is required for this post; however reasonable adjustments will be made for disabled individuals in line with the Equality Act 2010.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact Sarah McCartney, Rushcliffe Head of Service on either sarah.mccartney@nottshc.nhs.uk or 0115 9691300 Ext 17405 or 07768752150&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
